      <abstract>In the present article there is given a survey of series of works dedicated to
the study of compact global attractors of abstract dissipative dynamical
systems (botn autonomous and nonautonomous) and of some their applications.
Here there are touched on the questions that reflect scientific interests of
the author.


The research described in this publication was made possible in part by Award
No.MM1-3016 of the Moldovan Research and Development Association (MRDA) and
U.S. Civilian Research &amp; Development Foundation for the Independent States
of the Former Soviet Union (CRDF).</abstract>
      <title>Global Attractors of Dynamical Systems</title>
    </articleInfo>
