      <abstract>A class of multivariable nonlinear systems with a lagging argument is
considered. Such a systems often encounter when models of bialogical
or physical processes are constructed. Two solutions of stabilization
problem are received. The first solution is based on the nonlinear
stability transformation with lagging argument which provides the
Frobenious form for matrix of closed loop transformed system. The
second solution of stabilization problem is based on nonlinear
stability transformation with lagging argument which provides
 the Frobenious form with the last functional column only for the
object matrix of transformed system and the form of the first unit
orth for vector of control distribution of transformed system.

 The existence conditions and explicit form of both similarity
transformation are formed. The solution of stabilization problem
based on both similarity
transformation  is received in explicit form.</abstract>
      <title>Stabilization Problem Solution for One Class of Nonlinear Systems with a Lagging Argument</title>
    </articleInfo>
